WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:05.560
in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit. Amen!

00:00:05.560 --> 00:00:12.560
The reading from the Sinaxadion for April 29th, on which we commemorate,

00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:17.560
our Holy Father Basil, Bishop of Ostrog.

00:00:17.560 --> 00:00:23.560
Our Holy Father Basil was born in the year 1610 of poor but deeply devout parents

00:00:23.560 --> 00:00:27.560
in the village of Merconik in Herzegovina.

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:35.560
His first school of piety was his parental home, where the things of God were of more importance

00:00:35.560 --> 00:00:41.560
than earthly and fleeting cares, and the second in which his soul was able to satisfy

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:46.560
its spiritual aspirations was regular attendance at the divine liturgy,

00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:49.560
to which personal prayer and solitude was added.

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:54.560
When he entered a church, prostrating deeply to the ground and devoutly kissing it,

00:00:54.560 --> 00:01:01.560
he followed the divine liturgy, motionless, and with fear, as though he stood before the throne

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:08.560
of God. Although he was very poor, he always shared his bread with the other boys who went

00:01:08.560 --> 00:01:13.560
with him to keep the sheep. To escape the malign influence of those neighbors

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:19.560
who had apostatized from the Christian faith and converted to Islam, his parents sent him to finish

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:24.560
his education in the monastery of Zavala, of which his uncle was the abbot.

00:01:24.560 --> 00:01:30.560
Avidly reading the writings of the Holy Fathers, his heart burned for the ascetic life,

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:35.560
and he decided to become a monk. He was transferred in the monastery of Drosch,

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:40.560
and a short time later was ordained Deakin, and then priest.

00:01:40.560 --> 00:01:46.560
He was then called to serve with Metropolitan Mardarios of Satini.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:50.560
At this time, when the Serbs were oppressed under the Turkish Yoke,

00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:55.560
the Orthodox faith was also endangered by the propaganda of the Jesuits,

00:01:55.560 --> 00:01:58.560
who were seeking to convert them to Catholicism.

00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:04.560
St. Basil came to the Metropolitan's attention in connection with this cunning propaganda

00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:11.560
and the need to defend Orthodoxy. But the latter was indifferent and falsely accused him

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:19.560
in front of the people. These Calamnes found no echo because the Christians had full confidence

00:02:19.560 --> 00:02:25.560
in St. Basil, whose way of life was a radiant testimony to the truth.

00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:30.560
On his return to Drosch, the St. traveled round the villages, holding services

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:35.560
and exhorting the people to keep the faith as the most precious possession.

00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:42.560
This apostolic work stirred up against Basil the hatred of those who had become Muslims

00:02:42.560 --> 00:02:45.560
and they attempted to kill him.

00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:50.560
To escape this danger, the saint was forced to flee to Russia.

00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:56.560
He returned sometime later with a great many books and liturgical vestments.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:03:01.560
But he discovered that the hatred of the Muslims and the uniyods toward him

00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:09.560
had in no way abated, and he had to leave again, this time on a pilgrimage to mount Athos.

00:03:09.560 --> 00:03:17.560
On his return, he passed through Peck, where Paisios the Serbian Patriarch consecrated him Bishop

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:23.560
and named him Metropolitan of Thrabinje in the year 1638.

00:03:23.560 --> 00:03:29.560
The Metropolitan of Herzegovina being assassinated shortly afterwards by the Turks,

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:32.560
St. Basil was appointed to succeed him.

00:03:32.560 --> 00:03:38.560
Turkish oppression was at that time redoubling against the Serbian people.

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:45.560
Churches, monasteries and houses were sacked and the whole country was mercilessly devastated.

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:48.560
The Holy Bishop had once more to take flight.

00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:54.560
He found refuge in the monastery of Ostrog and settled in the cave that had been occupied

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:57.560
by the Holy Abbate Isaiah.

00:03:57.560 --> 00:04:02.560
From this retreat, he directed his diocese for fifteen years,

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:07.560
guiding himself by prayer and lengthy nocturnal intercession before God.

00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:11.560
He sometimes left the monastery to visit the afflicted people,

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:15.560
sympathizing with their sufferings and strengthening them in hope.

00:04:15.560 --> 00:04:20.560
Many there were who benefited from the miraculous power of his prayer,

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:24.560
and who already venerated him as a saint.

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:29.560
During the great waves of persecution, people went in crowds to Ostrog

00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:34.560
to receive spiritual and bodily comfort from the Holy Bishop.

00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:39.560
St. Basil had, in addition, to confront the malice of certain Orthodox,

00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:44.560
like Prince Raik and his sons, who inspired by the demon,

00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:50.560
caused great harm to the monastery and attempted to drive out the man of God.

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:56.560
Basil was patient and predicted to the Prince that all his sons would perish

00:04:56.560 --> 00:05:00.560
because of the ills done to the monastery.

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:07.560
When this prophecy was fulfilled, the Prince repented deeply and God gave him new issue.

00:05:07.560 --> 00:05:14.560
Indefatigable in his asceses and prayer by which he sustained his people,

00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:19.560
St. Basil entered peacefully into rest in the Lord on 29 April,

00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:22.560
in the year 1671.

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:28.560
At the moment of his last breath, an indescribable light filled his cell

00:05:28.560 --> 00:05:34.560
and then a vine sprouted up on the bare rock near the place where he died.

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:41.560
Many miracles began to be wrought at his grave and have never ceased to this day.

00:05:41.560 --> 00:05:47.560
Seven years after his death, St. Basil appeared in his sleep to the abbot

00:05:47.560 --> 00:05:53.560
of the monastery of St. Luke of Supa, clad in his episcopal vestments

00:05:53.560 --> 00:05:59.560
and with a censor in his hand, and told him to go and open his grave.

00:05:59.560 --> 00:06:04.560
While the saint was sensing, pieces of charcoal fell on the abbot,

00:06:04.560 --> 00:06:10.560
who woke full of fear and left immediately with his monks for Ostrog.

00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:15.560
When they opened the grave, they found the saint's body, the color of wax,

00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:19.560
and giving off a fragrance like that of Basil.

00:06:19.560 --> 00:06:26.560
They placed his relics in a reliquary in the church of the presentation of the mother of God in the temple,

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:31.560
where pilgrims were able from that time to venerate it.

00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:36.560
Just as the saint had never throughout his life known peace,

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:42.560
so his relics had to be hidden a number of times to escape Turkish dispoiling.

00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:48.560
In the year 1942, the monastery of Ostrog was bombed out.

00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:54.560
Thanks to the saint's protection, the projectiles fell without damaging the buildings.

00:06:54.560 --> 00:07:01.560
A shell even landed at the entrance of the saint's cave that had been transformed into a chapel,

00:07:01.560 --> 00:07:09.560
where his relics were placed, but it did not explode and can still be seen on that spot.

00:07:09.560 --> 00:07:14.560
Saint Basil is one of the most venerated saints among the Serbs.

00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:21.560
There are very many churches dedicated to him, both in Serbia and abroad.

00:07:21.560 --> 00:07:31.560
Through the prayers of our holy fathers, O Lord, Jesus Christ our God, have mercy on us and save us.
